flicts with an access, using PlaceConflictBias to handle ambiguous index comparisons conservatively.\n\n6. **Region Inference** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/nll.rs:113): The compute_regions function creates a RegionInferenceContext and manages polonius facts (if enabled). It then calls RegionInferenceContext::solve (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/region_infer/mod.rs:493), which solves all region constraints via constraint propagation and type checking to determine final region values.\n\n7. **Two-Phase Borrow Resolution** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs:1823): The check_activations method implements two-phase borrow checking. At activation points, it verifies that two-phase borrows don't interfere with other live borrows. Two-phase borrows act as shared borrows from reservation to activation point, then as mutable borrows afterward, allowing patterns like v.push(&mut v[0]).\n\nThe complete flow chains these components together: entry point → root context → constraint collection → region replacement → borrow gathering → type checking → liveness analysis → conflict detection → region solving → two-phase resolution, ensuring soundness of the borrow checker."
